&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organization:&lt;/strong&gt; Florida Panthers Hockey Club&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; Arena Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To:&lt;/strong&gt; Manager, Conversion Crew&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FLSA Status:&lt;/strong&gt; Non-Exempt (Hourly)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Part-Time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Amerant Bank Arena, Sunrise, FL — On-Site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt; Flexibility required for nights, overnights, weekends, and holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Job Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Conversion Crew is responsible for setting up, maintaining, converting, and preparing Amerant Bank Arena for events — including converting the facility back and forth between a professional hockey arena and a large-scale concert and event venue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert the arena between professional hockey and large-scale concert/event configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up seating arrangements and supporting furniture for concerts, hockey games, dinners, parties, and banquets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up signage, banners, and other conversion elements from one event or game to another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, repair, and remove arena parts and seating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to requests from management, vendors, guests, and event and team representatives to move furniture, boxes, and equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Satisfy requests from vendors, guests, and event representatives to relocate materials and equipment on event day and during events&lt;/li&gt;
